      "writtenOn": "2016-08-30T16:47:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would prefer calling this method createId. In Java is is highly idiomatic that get/set are assoicated with either returning a private variable, or setting it via getter and setter methods. In this method, you aren\u0027t setting or getting a private variable, you are generating a dimension ID.\n\nAlso, do you really need this method at all, since all getId does is call generateDimensionId. Could you just have one static method called createDimensionId?",
      "revId": "29efe178689bbbef57eeae3d4e3ef98a96f78bcd",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
