      "writtenOn": "2016-08-30T16:47:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since you\u0027ve introduced the new helpers class that I mentioned, I\u0027m wondering if a better alternative would have been create a base class DimensionsBase that inherits from AbstractEntity, and then derive DimensionsNames and DimensionsValues from DimensionsBase. That would resolve the inheritance of DimensionsValues from DimensionsBase, but I\u0027m not sure if you will end-up with as much code sharing.",
      "revId": "29efe178689bbbef57eeae3d4e3ef98a96f78bcd",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa7ab95a_a352f932",
        "filename": "java/src/main/java/monasca/api/domain/model/dimension/DimensionNames.java",
        "patchSetId": 26
      },
      "lineNbr": 47,
      "author": {
        "id": 2419
