      "writtenOn": "2016-08-30T16:47:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So, you invoke the helper in DimensionHelpers, which generates the ID if it is null and returns the ID. However, id is never assigned, so it will always be null right?\n\nHow about if the helper just generates the ID. it should depend on whether something passed into it is null or not. That test can be done here.\n\nif this.id \u003d\u003d null {\n    this.id \u003d helper.generateId(\"metricName\u003d\" + metricName)\n}\nreturn this.id\n\nAnd since the only thing that the id depends on is the metricName, and that is known in the constructor, you could easily just assign id there and not test if it is null here.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 47,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 47,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "29efe178689bbbef57eeae3d4e3ef98a96f78bcd",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
